  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c6c0abd7-7fff-4003-1bb3-c01ebd2e59ee\"></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">The proposed outrigger roof extension, by reason of its scale, massing, design and position, would comprise an overbearing, incongruous and disproportionate addition to the host building and wider terrace, that would overwhelm and subsume the rear elevation of the host building and would fail to respect the established pattern of development in the area. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach)&nbsp; and D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the recommendations of the Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Extensions and Alterations (2009).&nbsp;</span></p>",
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ad80cc88-7fff-9d6b-4850-fc70f4bbb52e\"></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ad80cc88-7fff-9d6b-4850-fc70f4bbb52e\"></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">The proposed outrigger roof extension, by reason of its inappropriate scale, positioning and design, would comprise an overbearing feature that will give rise to an increased sense of enclosure and overshadowing impacts to the residential amenity and living conditions of adjoining 100 Blurton Road, contrary to Hackney’s LP33 policy LP2 (Development and Amenity), London Plan (2021) policy D3 ‘Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach’ and the Council’s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD</span></p>"
  ],
